**Issue:** Without a custom error handler, Express's default handler can expose stack traces and internal implementation details in error responses (**OWASP A09:2021 – Security Logging and Monitoring Failures**).

**Fix:** Add an error-handling middleware as the last `app.use()` call:

```js
// Must be defined AFTER all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log the full error internally (to your logging system)
  console.error({
    message: err.message,
    stack: err.stack,
    url: req.url,
    method: req.method,
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  });

  // Return a sanitized message to the client — never expose stack traces
  const statusCode = err.status || err.statusCode || 500;
  res.status(statusCode).json({
    error: statusCode < 500 ? err.message : 'An internal server error occurred',
  });
});
```

